
The Blue Devils and the overall field hockey program at Davis Senior High School have built a tradition of excellence over the years with over 10 league titles to their name.  The program strives to provide a positive team environment, with a focus on teamwork, dedication, respect, sportsmanship, fun and pride.  Field hockey is a fall sport, however there are several opportunities to play and learn throughout the season, including spring clinics, a summer camp for 6th through 10th graders, and July Night clinics.  The head coach of the program is Varsity coach Katy Loge.  Meryl Craig is the JV coach.
